sentences: Joy Oladokun (born 1992) is an American singer-songwriter.
She has released three studio albums; Carry (2016),
In Defense of My Own Happiness (The Beginnings) (2020), and In Defense of My Own Happiness  (2021).

In 2015, Joy Oladokun self-released her debut EP Cathedrals.
Her debut studio album, Carry Me was funded by Kickstarter and released on April 29, 2016 through Well Records.

NPR listed "I See America" on its 100 Best Songs of 2020.
On July 17, 2020, Oladokun released her second studio album, In Defense of My Own Happiness (Vol. 1) with White Boy Records.
